content:
From: JS Lemay <js.lemay@mq.edu.au>

From: Richard Blute <rblute@uottawa.ca>
Sent: Saturday, October 28, 2023 12:01:18 AM (UTC+10:00) Canberra, Melbourne, Sydney
To: Categories mailing list <categories@mq.edu.au>
Subject: Octoberfest Final Announcement. It's tomorrow.

The 2023 Category Theory Octoberfest will be held on the weekend of October 28th through October 29th. The meeting will be virtual. Following the tradition of past Octoberfests, this is intended to be an informal meeting, covering all areas of category theory and its applications. Here is the official conference website:

https://richardblute.ca/octoberfest-2023/<https://protect-au.mimecast.com/s/ZsfjCr810kCMEW9qc7qVlY?domain=richardblute.ca/>

At the moment, you'll find there the schedule with all speakers, titles and abstracts, as well as the zoom link which will be the same for both days.

For further questions, feel free to contact me. Hope to see you there.

cheers
Rick Blute
